<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Whether this taxon belongs to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Microdontinae">Microdontinae</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName family="Syrphidae" lsidName="" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="family">Syrphidae</taxonomicName>
at all is uncertain. It was described from larvae found in an ants nest (
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, WM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="237 - 244" title="Two extraordinary larval myrmecophiles from Panama." url="10.1073/pnas.10.6.237" volume="10" year="1924">Wheeler 1924</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng, X-Y" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="21 - 48" title="A generic conspectus of the Microdontinae (Diptera: Syrphidae) with the description of two new genera from Africa and China." volume="1879" year="2008">Cheng and Thompson (2008)</bibRefCitation>
suspect it belongs to another family, perhaps 
<taxonomicName family="Phoridae" lsidName="" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="family">Phoridae</taxonomicName>
. Photographs of a larva can be found at http://syrphidae.lifedesks.org/pages/25523.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
